PRAYER ON THE EIFFEL TOWER</i>

22
00:06:04,598 --> 00:06:06,407
1st May 1962, rue des Patriarches

23
00:06:06,633 --> 00:06:08,840
It's boring
when you work in this heat...

24
00:06:08,902 --> 00:06:11,508
It's no fun, you slave away.

25
00:06:11,671 --> 00:06:13,582
For my wife, one thing counts.

26
00:06:13,740 --> 00:06:15,413
"How much did you make?"

27
00:06:15,575 --> 00:06:17,521
She loves me for what I earn.

28
00:06:17,677 --> 00:06:20,886
Between my boss bawling me out
and my wife...

29
00:06:21,047 --> 00:06:23,618
I'm at peace commuting.
But now I drive in.

30
00:06:23,783 --> 00:06:25,456
I'm not at peace anymore.

31
00:06:25,619 --> 00:06:27,064
When are you free?

32
00:06:27,721 --> 00:06:30,395
When I'm driving in light traffic.

33
00:06:30,924 --> 00:06:33,632
Because I work, work, work.

34
00:06:33,793 --> 00:06:34,931
Sundays, Mondays, Saturdays.

35
00:06:35,095 --> 00:06:38,474
Why? For money.
I have loans, rent, all that.

36
00:06:38,632 --> 00:06:40,043
I gotta keep working.

37
00:06:40,834 --> 00:06:42,780
Some guys earn less than me.

38
00:06:42,936 --> 00:06:45,849
Doing what hours?
9 am to 6 pm.

39
00:06:46,606 --> 00:06:48,950
- And you?
- 9 am to 8 pm.

40
00:06:49,109 --> 00:06:51,111
And I'm always on my feet.

41
00:06:51,478 --> 00:06:54,584
You can't do it for long,
stay on your feet.

42
00:06:54,748 --> 00:06:56,159
After 8 you're free?

43
00:06:56,516 --> 00:06:58,792
Free to get yelled at by my wife?

44
00:06:59,753 --> 00:07:01,426
Free for what?
Home at 8.

45
00:07:01,588 --> 00:07:02,623
At 8.30 I eat.

46
00:07:02,789 --> 00:07:05,167
At 9, turn on the TV.
We're fine.

47
00:07:05,525 --> 00:07:07,402
We both watch on our own.

48
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:08,561
So we don't talk.

49
00:07:08,728 --> 00:07:09,934
If I fidget, she says:

50
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:11,837
"Sit still.
Turn the TV off."

51
00:07:11,998 --> 00:07:14,410
When I get home:
"I'm so tired."

52
00:07:14,567 --> 00:07:16,171
I say:
"Yes, you're tired."

53
00:07:16,536 --> 00:07:18,482
Lucky there aren't two.

54
00:07:18,638 --> 00:07:19,480
Two what?

55
00:07:19,639 --> 00:07:20,617
Two channels.

56
00:07:20,774 --> 00:07:21,980
You'd have to choose.

57
00:07:22,142 --> 00:07:25,089
I'd buy two sets
and work harder.

58
00:07:26,813 --> 00:07:27,917
And vacations'?

59
00:07:28,114 --> 00:07:29,787
I go to Italy.

60
00:07:29,916 --> 00:07:30,917
To Italy.

61
00:07:31,084 --> 00:07:32,586
You're free then?

62
00:07:32,752 --> 00:07:35,528
No, a peaceful vacation is no good.

63
00:07:35,689 --> 00:07:37,498
I need noise. I dance all night.

64
00:07:37,657 --> 00:07:39,034
Daytime I rest in bed.

65
00:07:39,192 --> 00:07:40,694
Daytime, I don't know...

66
00:07:40,860 --> 00:07:43,466
My wife looks after the kids.

67
00:07:43,630 --> 00:07:45,576
So I have some freedom, not much.

68
00:07:45,732 --> 00:07:46,710
When are you happy?

69
00:07:46,866 --> 00:07:48,539
When am I happy?

70
00:07:48,702 --> 00:07:49,942
When I sell a suit.

71
00:07:50,837 --> 00:07:51,907
Cash in the till.

72
00:07:52,072 --> 00:07:54,074
Lots of cash in the till.

73
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:56,151
All that counts is cash.

74
00:07:56,509 --> 00:07:59,217
- That's all?
- Sell, sell, sell. That's all.

75
00:07:59,579 --> 00:08:00,751
And the kids' health.

76
00:08:00,914 --> 00:08:01,858
Knock on wood.

77
00:08:02,015 --> 00:08:04,086
When the kids are healthy.

78
00:08:04,250 --> 00:08:05,558
I'm not worried.

79
00:08:05,719 --> 00:08:08,632
What matters is cash in the till.

80
00:08:09,055 --> 00:08:11,934
And then what?
You put it in to take it out.

81
00:08:12,092 --> 00:08:13,036
How come?

82
00:08:13,193 --> 00:08:14,194
To use it.

83
00:08:14,561 --> 00:08:16,165
I buy more suits.

84
00:08:17,664 --> 00:08:18,836
Not much margin.

85
00:08:18,999 --> 00:08:20,535
That's modern society.

86
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:23,704
For me: suits,
for others: cars or movies.

87
00:08:23,870 --> 00:08:24,940
Like your work.

88
00:08:25,105 --> 00:08:27,051
Why produce a movie?
To make another.

89
00:08:27,207 --> 00:08:29,813
What do you do with the money'?

90
00:08:29,976 --> 00:08:31,751
You do the opposite now'?

91
00:08:31,911 --> 00:08:33,185
I wouldn't say that.

92
00:08:33,546 --> 00:08:34,251
So why do you want...

93
00:08:34,614 --> 00:08:36,059
I buy suits.

94
00:08:36,216 --> 00:08:37,194
You go to movies.

95
00:08:37,550 --> 00:08:38,756
Me, movies?

96
00:08:38,918 --> 00:08:39,988
There isn't much on.

97
00:08:40,153 --> 00:08:41,223
Not much on?

98
00:08:41,588 --> 00:08:42,225
What's on now'?

99
00:08:42,589 --> 00:08:43,567
<i>Cleo from 5 to 7.</i>

100
00:08:43,723 --> 00:08:44,667
I'll go see it.

101
00:08:44,824 --> 00:08:45,700
<i>And Marienbad.</i>

102
00:08:45,859 --> 00:08:46,997
" <i>Marienbad"?
Oh,</i> no...

103
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:48,104
A bit too...

104
00:08:48,261 --> 00:08:49,865
I'm a simple guy.

105
00:08:50,030 --> 00:08:50,940
I'm sorry.

106
00:08:51,097 --> 00:08:52,906
Who says it's for intellects?

107
00:08:53,066 --> 00:08:56,275
You have to figure it out, and I...

108
00:08:56,636 --> 00:08:57,979
You understand stuff'?

109
00:08:58,138 --> 00:08:59,674
I won't rack my brains.

110
00:08:59,839 --> 00:09:02,683
Why fork out money
to figure things out?

111
00:09:02,842 --> 00:09:03,946
Isn't it nice?

112
00:09:04,110 --> 00:09:06,818
Sitting racking my brains,

113
00:09:06,980 --> 00:09:07,890
isn't worth it.

114
00:09:08,048 --> 00:09:09,550
I like these movies:

115
00:09:09,716 --> 00:09:11,889
when stylish people pull pistols,

116
00:09:12,052 --> 00:09:14,089
shoot each other, then make calls.

117
00:09:14,254 --> 00:09:16,256
And I like...

118
00:09:16,623 --> 00:09:18,000
I like historical movies.

119
00:09:18,158 --> 00:09:20,001
You prefer killing or calling?

120
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:21,935
Killing, then calling.

121
00:09:22,095 --> 00:09:23,199
Why do you like it?

122
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:25,873
Why?
I like watching Superman.

123
00:09:26,032 --> 00:09:28,137
I have a hang-up: I'm dumpy.

124
00:09:28,301 --> 00:09:30,281
I like seeing the beefcake

125
00:09:30,637 --> 00:09:32,241
bust everything up.

126
00:09:32,605 --> 00:09:33,845
Mind being different?

127
00:09:34,007 --> 00:09:35,714
It's liberating.

128
00:09:35,875 --> 00:09:36,751
In what way?

129
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:38,651
I think: "If I was like him..."

130
00:09:38,812 --> 00:09:41,884
And at night, I think:
"I'd have done this..."

131
00:09:42,048 --> 00:09:43,652
But you're not like him?

132
00:09:43,817 --> 00:09:46,855
I'm not hung-up.

133
00:09:47,020 --> 00:09:50,661
So long as I eat well and sleep well...

134
00:09:50,824 --> 00:09:53,737
I eat well, sleep well
and turn in early.

135
00:09:53,893 --> 00:09:55,736
- So you're happy?
- Right.

136
00:09:55,895 --> 00:09:57,169
You said you weren't.

137
00:09:57,330 --> 00:10:00,277
When I eat and sleep
and the till is full.

138
00:10:01,334 --> 00:10:03,678
Is that your aim in life?

139
00:10:03,837 --> 00:10:04,781
I need it.

140
00:10:04,938 --> 00:10:06,076
Let's not talk politics,

141
00:10:06,239 --> 00:10:09,345
liberty, equality, fraternity, OK.

142
00:10:09,709 --> 00:10:10,915
Why not politics?

143
00:10:11,077 --> 00:10:12,647
Politics, politics...

144
00:10:12,812 --> 00:10:15,019
Politics for me, is living well.

145
00:10:15,181 --> 00:10:16,888
If we say I must be free,

146
00:10:17,050 --> 00:10:18,723
my wife and kids free,

147
00:10:18,885 --> 00:10:20,091
that's politics.

148
00:10:20,253 --> 00:10:23,894
It's another topic.
We can discuss it forever.

149
00:10:24,157 --> 00:10:26,967
We can do things too.
Get political?

150
00:10:27,127 --> 00:10:28,367
What kind of politics?

151
00:10:28,728 --> 00:10:30,332
Should we make changes?

152
00:10:30,697 --> 00:10:33,007
It must remain representative.

153
00:10:33,166 --> 00:10:36,147
We elect parliamentarians
and they vote for us.

154
00:10:36,302 --> 00:10:40,307
You have a traffic ticket,
you write to Mr. Le Pen or Mr. Thorez:

155
00:10:40,673 --> 00:10:43,381
"I voted for you,
can you cancel this fine?"

156
00:10:43,743 --> 00:10:45,882
A limited idea of democracy.

157
00:10:46,045 --> 00:10:49,356
Not at all.
Parliamentarians who defend us.

158
00:10:49,716 --> 00:10:51,320
No point having more.

159
00:10:51,684 --> 00:10:52,754
Nothing more'?

160
00:10:52,919 --> 00:10:55,695
We haven't done too badly
till now.

161
00:10:55,922 --> 00:10:59,836
What harm has de Gaulle
done me since 1958?

162
00:10:59,993 --> 00:11:00,835
None.

163
00:11:00,994 --> 00:11:03,668
Personally, speaking for myself,

164
00:11:03,830 --> 00:11:05,810
he's done me no harm.

165
00:11:05,965 --> 00:11:07,672
You'll say I'm selfish.

166
00:11:07,867 --> 00:11:09,847
But if 40 million selfish
Frenchmen unite,

167
00:11:10,003 --> 00:11:11,277
we'd have politics.

168
00:12:48,534 --> 00:12:50,309
A snack on the grass,

169
00:12:50,470 --> 00:12:52,882
a picnic with your old lady...

170
00:12:53,039 --> 00:12:54,347
You get the idea.

171
00:12:55,508 --> 00:12:57,351
Her little transistor radio...

172
00:12:58,211 --> 00:12:59,815
Be happy, have a drink...

173
00:12:59,979 --> 00:13:01,925
Enjoy a nice time.

174
00:13:02,081 --> 00:13:05,392
If you had time and money,
would you have a TV?

175
00:13:05,551 --> 00:13:07,792
TV'? Sure would!

176
00:13:07,954 --> 00:13:08,796
You bet.

177
00:13:08,955 --> 00:13:12,027
- Here in the shop?
- No, not down here.

178
00:13:12,191 --> 00:13:14,330
In the apartment, upstairs.

179
00:13:14,494 --> 00:13:16,906
It's a must, isn't it.

180
00:13:17,063 --> 00:13:19,100
Live life to the fullest.

181
00:13:19,265 --> 00:13:21,336
We have the time.

182
00:13:21,501 --> 00:13:23,378
You see it as a funeral?

183
00:13:23,536 --> 00:13:26,346
Yeah, a bit like the song.

184
